Cell.Text: [S] Good question. Hard to say. | I... I can't really tell. | I feel like it was a long time. Who is Skyrim's High King?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02SeranaBackground1Topic: How long were you in there?

Cell.Text: Oh, great. A war of succession. Good to know the world didn't get boring while I was gone. | Who are the contenders?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02BackgroundTimeHighKingWhatNow: That's actually a matter for debate.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Empire? What... what empire?
The Empire supports Elisif, and killed Ulfric for his rebellion.
<<Shared>> Empire? What... what empire?
The Empire supported Elisif, but Ulfric now controls Skyrim.
<<Shared>> Empire? What... what empire?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02BackgroundTimeHighKingRejoin: The Empire supports Elisif, but there are many in Skyrim loyal to Ulfric.

Cell.Text: [S] Septim? Oh my. | I don't even know that name. | I must have been gone longer than I thought. Definitely longer than we planned. | Please, let's hurry. I need to get home so I can figure out what's happened.
I've... never heard of him. Is he well supported?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02BackgroundTimeHighKingUlfric: Ulfric Stormcloak is the true High King.

Cell.Text: I don't know that name. You say she's Jarl of Solitude? Who supports her?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02TimeHighQueenElisif: Elisif of Solitude will be High Queen.

Cell.Text: I'd... rather not get into that with you. If that's all right. | I'm sorry, it's not that... it's just that I don't know who I can trust just yet. | Let's get to my home, and I'll have a better sense of where we all stand.
It's on an island near Solitude. Hopefully we can find a boat to take us there. | It's my family home. Not the most welcoming place, but depending on who's around, I'll be safe there.
This is your home?
This is it. Home sweet... castle.
[S] Let's just say that my mother and father had a bit of a falling out. | Don't worry, I'm not in any danger or anything like that. It'll just be more unpleasant to run into my father.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02SeranaBackground3A: Why wouldn't you be safe there?

Cell.Text: My father and I don't really get along. | Ugh, saying it out loud makes it sound so... common. "Little girl who doesn't get along with her father." Read that story a hundred times.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02SeranaBackground3B: Someone you don't want to see?

Cell.Text: [S] I didn't want you to think I was one of those... you know, the women who just sit in their castle all day? | I don't know. Coming from a place like this, well... it's not really me. I hope you can believe that.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02SeranaBackground3C: Why didn't you tell me it was so huge?

Cell.Text: It's something all right.
I wasn't sure you'd come back for me. I'm still looking for a guide to get me home. What do you say?
[S] I'm right behind you.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02SeranaStage5AbandonedTopic2: That's why I'm here. Let's go.

Cell.Text: I'll be here if you change your mind.
Yes, it is, and it's mine.
It's... complicated. I can't really talk about. I'm sorry.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02ElderScrollWhy: Why do you have an Elder Scroll?

Cell.Text: Ha. Nothing can destroy an Elder Scroll. Worry more about protecting your hide, and let me worry about my things.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02ElderScrollWhat: Is it fragile? Do we need to be careful with it?
